      "Injured Person evacuated to emergency clinic in Cameron, Louisiana",
      "BSEE investigation conducted",
      "Injured Person returned to Full Duty on 24-JUN-2019"
    ],
    "summary": "On 6 May 2019 at 19:35 hours, a Floor Hand on the Enterprise 263 jack-up drilling rig sustained a left thumb and finger injury when four-inch elevators being installed onto bails rolled out and fell to the rig floor. Poor weather conditions, sea state, and rig elevation caused rig sway that allowed the elevators to roll out of the bails while the worker was removing a nut and bolt from the elevator ears. The worker was not wearing required impact gloves and did not have proper hand placement.",
